bio: Professor Aaron Quigley is Head of School in Computer Science and Engineering at the University of New South Wales (UNSW) in Australia and is an ACM Distinguished Member and a Senior Member of IEEE. He is the technical program chair for the ACM EICS conference in 2022 and he co-chaired the ACM CHI Conference in 2021. He is a member of the ACM CHI conference steering committee and the ACM Europe Council Conferences Working Group.
institution: School of Computer Science and Engineering, The University of New South Wales

title: Aaron Quigley
